  "title": "Technical & Specification Executive/Manager",
  "description": "<p><ul><li>Identify and target architectural firms, design consultants, and project stakeholders relevant to the company’s product portfolio</li></ul></p><ul><li><p>Schedule and conduct meetings with architects and designers to present products for project specification</p></li><li><p>Understand project requirements, design intent, performance criteria, and budget constraints</p></li><li><p>Recommend suitable products and systems for inclusion in project specifications</p></li><li><p>Provide technical presentations, samples, mock-ups, and product demonstrations</p></li><li><p>Support architects with technical data, drawings, BIM objects, certifications, and compliance documentation</p></li><li><p>Follow up to ensure products are written into specifications, schedules, and tender documents</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal technical, sales, and project teams to support specification success</p></li><li><p>Track project pipelines from concept through tender and construction stages</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong professional relationships with architects, consultants, and key decision-makers</p></li><li><p>Gather market intelligence on upcoming projects, competitors, and specification trends</p></li></ul>",
